#week-title("Four", "Tarot as Alchemical Spread & Year Review")

=== Core Teaching

The Tarot is not just for looking at cards; it is for *reading* the state of the
Work. The four suits of the Minor Arcana correspond to the four worlds of the
Qabalah:
- *Wands:* Atziluth (Archetypal World).
- *Cups:* Briah (Creative World).
- *Swords:* Yetzirah (Formative World).
- *Pentacles:* Assiah (Material World).

By laying a spread, the alchemist can mirror the current condition of their
laboratory and their own psyche, revealing where the fire is balanced and where
the Work is stalled.

=== Topics This Week

- The four worlds of the Qabalah and the four Tarot suits
- Constructing a spread for laboratory review
- Reading the "Alchemical Mirror"

#inner-work[
  *The Ten-Card Year Spread*

  Conduct a ten-card spread at the end of this week, reviewing your first six
  months of study.

  *The Practice:*
  Layout the cards in the form of the Tree of Life (1 at the top, 10 at the
  bottom).
  1. Kether: The original intention.
  2. Chokmah: The initial inspiration.
  3. Binah: The discipline established.
  ...and so on down to Malkuth: The physical result so far.

  What does the reading reveal about where you stand in your own work? Record the
  layout and your interpretation in your Tarot journal.
]

